  "text": "The principal acknowledged the positive impact that the school had on him. Reciprocal-effects models in particular hypothesise that relationship between the principal and the features of the school are interactive, which implies that principals adapt to schools and change their behaviour and thinking over time [CITATION_1] . It was in particular his leadership style that the principal realised he needed to be adapted. However, as in Garchinsky's study (2008:127) , the principal experienced some challenges in becoming a more \"collaborative leader\".",
